freeTextConditions.note:
LEVIES
* Levy amount : 200.00 AUD and Description : test. Payable direct in destination.

SPECIAL NOTES
Conditions: This is not a child-friendly experience. Children between the ages of 6 years and 13 years are not permitted on this tour.

INCLUDES
Guide: Guided minibus tour Cave Tour: A short caving tour is included (April & May)

ITINERARY TEXT
Day 1: Reykjavik to Snaefellsjokull National Park The tour begins with collection from your hotel in Reykjavik and progress west towards Snaefellsness peninsula, following a scenic route of dramatic landscapes. We will make a short stop for refreshments, allowing you to pick up supplies for the day ahead. The peninsula is home to varied wildlife, including many types of bird and even a seal colony. We stop at a black sand beach near Ytri-Tunga farm, offering an opportunity to spot some of these playful residents. Next up is a visit to the idyllic Arnarstapi village where you'll take a walk through extraordinary landscape along the precipitous shoreline toward the small village of Hellnar. Here we will break for lunch. In the afternoon the tour continues to Vatnshellir lava cave located in the Snaefellsjokull National Park, close to the glacier which is the setting Jules Verne chose for the start of his famous adventure. The cave is optional (see option price when booking). If you do not book the caving tour, you can take a short walk around the area with your guide while the other guests go caving. Note that you can also wait in the car if you want. Day 2: Exploring Vatnshellir You'll descend into a subterranean world of stalactites, stalagmites, and strange lava formations. The glow of your headlight may form eerie shapes and shadows, which dance across the walls of the cave. The caving is short, very easy, and suitable for everyone. From the curious underworld of Vatnshellir, we continue to Djupalonssandur, a black-pebbled beach that offers stark views out to the sea and fascinating histories of shipwrecks and adventure. Departing Djupalonssandur beach we travel past impressive landscapes, towards the northern side of Snaefellsnes peninsula. Grundarfjorour fishing village is the next stop. Surrounded by particularly beautiful mountains. The area is home to one of the peninsula's most photographed iconic landmarks Kirkjufell. This symmetrical mountain towers 463 m (1519 ft) up from the shoreline, "church mount" is it's name translated to English and you can see why. Out of Grundarfjorour the route lies across a lava field named Berserkjahraun. According to Viking legends this is the place where two Swedish "berserkers" forged Iceland's first road and over to the south side of the peninsula through a highland pass. On the way a short stop is made at a viewpoint where you can take a short walk down to a small and beautiful waterfall. Heading back to Reykjavik, we have time to take in the Natural Heritage Site of Gerouberg, home to a beautiful belt of basalt columns in impossibly geometric shapes. Finally, we drop-off to your hotel, allowing the day's magic to sink in deep.

DESCRIPTION
Snaefellsnes Peninsula is a world of diversity, comprising many of Iceland's unique features on one peninsula. It is a legendary area of magic and beauty, immortalized in Jules Verne's Journey to the Centre of the Earth. We will also visit a cave on the way. If you don't see the wonder of being literally inside a volcano, you should choose another activity. But if you go, you'll have one of the most amazing experiences of your life. The hike across the lava field is work, the ride down will make your heart beat. But you'll never forget it. The hike is a great way to start the tour, it?s the perfect build up. The inside of the volcano is amazing it?s a chance to get a visual understanding of how the earth is made, you can really feel the earths age. Well, there's only one volcano in the world not clogged by lava, the majestic Thrihnukagigur of Iceland. A true descent to the centre of the earth. You are left in the darkness to explore, touch, and hear the insides of a dormant chamber. No words can describe the adventure. Simply stunning.

HIGHLIGHTS
Real-life Journey to the Center of the Earth Visit Inside the Volcano Snfellsnes Peninsula Snaefellsnesjokull National Park Djupalonssandur Beach Berserkjahraun Lava Field Vatnhellir Cave Arnarstapi VillageKirkjufell Mountain

DROPOFF NOTES
